//🔥💲🍕 Height vs Nodes for binary-tree  🍕💲🔥
// as mtlb apn tree ki kisi ek particular-constant "height" k liyeh uss tree meh Possible-Minimum-and-Maximum "no.-of-nodes" dekhenge ki agr given height "h" hai toh mtlb voh "h"-height ka tree minimumly-kitne nodes se ya meh ban skta hai and maximumly-kitne ka ban skta hai mtlb uss "h"-height-tree meh minimum kitne nodes ho sktehh hai and maximum-kitne-nodes ho sktehh hai, as toh mtlb apn yeh dekhenge..

// So toh mtlb for the given height-("h") k liyeh simply formulas are.. :-
// 1. Minimum-no.-of-nodes (n-min) is = h+1
// 2. Maximum-no.-of-nodes (n-max) = 2^(h+1)-1
//👿📔imp-Note-point:-As toh ess forumale meh apn simply height ki value likhenge or apnko minimum-no.-of-nodes mil jayenge and or maximum-no.-of-nodes bhi mil jayenge..
//📔📔Note-point:- as height-measurement meh "root-node" ko height-meh nhi gintehh hai , as "level"-measuring meh "root-node"-level ko Count kretehh hai.
